@thepathnotfound AMD's drivers have been solid for a long time. We're well past the omega drivers era..

I record game play just as well in AMD's software as I do in Nvidia etc.

I run AMD and NVidia cards on different machines. I've seen people blaming antilag for getting banned in games I played. I and my friends had no issue on our AMD machines. So I can't help but be suspicious because it's not like cheaters don't always blame everyone and everything else when banned.

@hezekiahconley7807 but how is that going to happen? There are only 2 companies to choose from, and they are 1 of the top 3 richest companies in the world. And even if pc builders stopped buying, what share of the market is that really? I imagine most people are buying prebuilt computers, and that gives them even more power. Not to mention laptops. No one is building laptops. They hold all of the cards here, and there is no "invisible hand". The hand controlling the market is very visible, and it's not us by design, a design we let happen. Consumers alone are not going to be organized enough to stop Nvidia from doing what they want to do imo.

And all of this is completely avoidable. Conservatives have spent decades telling people the government is ineffectual by MAKING the government that way, but this is exactly the type of thing governments are set up to do, and they are perfectly capable of doing it. 

When people say politics doesn't matter, it's because we let it happen. We continuously let people in power who undermine the government and deregulate corporations to create these exact situations, and then are shocked when corporations win. Traditional supply and demand is not going to be enough to stop this from happening if people don't show up and vote in people that setup guardrails from this happening.

